# 📡 FitTrack API Documentation

**Base URL**: `https://fittrack-api.onrender.com/api`

This RESTful API supports the core backend of the FitTrack application, allowing users to manage workouts, meals, user authentication, and progress tracking.

---

## 🔐 Auth Routes

### POST `/auth/register`
- Registers a new user.
- **Request Body:**
  ```json
  {
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "jane@example.com",
    "password": "securepassword"
  }
Response:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "message": "User created successfully",
  "token": "<JWT_TOKEN>"
}
POST /auth/login
Authenticates user credentials and returns a token.

Request Body:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword"
}
Response:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "token": "<JWT_TOKEN>"
}
🧑‍💪 Workouts
GET /workouts
Retrieves all workouts for the logged-in user.

Headers: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

POST /workouts
Logs a new workout.

Headers: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

Request Body:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "type": "Running",
  "duration": 30,
  "caloriesBurned": 250,
  "date": "2025-07-15"
}
🍽️ Meals
GET /meals
Returns all meals logged by the user.

Headers: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

POST /meals
Adds a new meal entry.

Headers: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

Request Body:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "name": "Lunch",
  "calories": 600,
  "protein": 30,
  "date": "2025-07-15"
}
📈 Progress
GET /progress
Returns overall progress statistics.

Headers: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

Response:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "totalWorkouts": 42,
  "totalCaloriesBurned": 8500,
  "weeklySummary": [
    {
      "week": "2025-Week-28",
      "workouts": 4,
      "meals": 21,
      "caloriesIntake": 12500,
      "caloriesBurned": 1500
    }
  ]
}
⚙️ Categories (Optional)
GET /categories
Returns workout and meal categories.

🛑 Error Responses
401 Unauthorized – Invalid or missing JWT token

400 Bad Request – Invalid input data

500 Internal Server Error – Server failure

